## ✅ Recommended Actions

### Option A: Request Santi to Rebase and Clean Up (Preferred)
1. Have him **rebase onto latest main** (`git rebase origin/main`)
2. During rebase, conflicts should be resolved by **keeping main's version** for files he didn't intentionally change
3. Remove `ChatbotPage.jsx` and the `/chatbot` route (conflicts with floating widget architecture)
4. Migrate his `learning-*` CSS classes into proper **CSS Modules** (`.module.css`) files
5. Remove duplicate `.gitignore` entries
6. Squash the 58 commits into logical, reviewable units

### Option B: Cherry-Pick Only the Valuable Work
If the rebase is too messy, cherry-pick only the commits that add **genuine new functionality**:
- Learning feed service + edge function
- Certification exam review features
- Slug-based navigation (if desired)
- Progress status management

### Option C: Block the Merge, Review File-by-File
Request changes on the PR and review each of the 44 changed files, accepting only the changes that align with your architecture.

---

> [!TIP]
> The root cause is that Santi branched from `agus_cap_ux` (which contained a lot of history including your work) and never rebased onto main. When he finally merged main in, he resolved all conflicts in favor of his branch. A conversation about **rebasing workflow** and **CSS Module standards** would prevent this in the future.
